CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*cfi->cfiq)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct cfi_ident)...)
#47: FILE: drivers/mtd/chips/cfi_probe.c:206:
+	cfi->cfiq = kzalloc(sizeof(struct cfi_ident) + num_erase_regions * 4, GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

